19.97. Let G be an m-generated group the elementary theory of which Th(G) coincides with the elementary theory Th(F) of a free soluble group F of derived length n ⩾3 of finite rank r ⩾2. Must the groups G and F be isomorphic?
The answer is affirmative if m ⩽r or n = 2
E. I. Timoshenko
